<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q11_v13" title="Q11_v13" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceC</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>En una tarjeta técnica de una ampolleta se indica la siguiente relación entre el consumo eléctrico total E (en watt-hora, Wh) y el número de horas h que permanece encendida:</p>
    <div>
      <m:math>
        <m:mi>E</m:mi>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mn>15</m:mn>
        <m:mo>·</m:mo>
        <m:mi>h</m:mi>
      </m:math>
    </div>
    <p>En la misma tarjeta se aclara que h es el número de horas que la ampolleta permanece encendida y que E es el consumo total de energía en Wh. Además, se indica la siguiente equivalencia de unidades:</p>
    <p>
      <m:math>
        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
        <m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext>
        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
        <m:mn>1000</m:mn>
        <m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext>
      </m:math>
    </p>
    <p>Si esta ampolleta permanece encendida durante 220 horas, ¿cuántos kilowatt-hora (kWh) consume en total?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-Choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">3 300 000 kWh<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Con <m:math><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn></m:math>, se obtiene <m:math><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext></m:math>. Luego, como <m:math><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>, resulta <m:math><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3,3</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>, no <m:math><m:mn>3 300 000</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">3300 kWh<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar <m:math><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn></m:math>, se obtiene <m:math><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext></m:math>. Ese valor está en Wh, no en kWh. Al convertir: <m:math><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3,3</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>. Por lo tanto, <m:math><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math> no corresponde.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">3,3 kWh<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Con <m:math><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn></m:math>, se calcula <m:math><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>, entonces <m:math><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3,3</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">0,33 kWh<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Primero, <m:math><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>15</m:mn><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext></m:math>. Luego, al convertir a kWh se divide por <m:math><m:mn>1000</m:mn></m:math>: <m:math><m:mn>3300</m:mn><m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext><m:mo>÷</m:mo><m:mn>1000</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3,3</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math>. Por eso, <m:math><m:mn>0,33</m:mn><m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext></m:math> es menor que el consumo real.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Usar la relación entre consumo y horas</strong></p>
            <p>La tarjeta indica:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>E</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>15</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mi>h</m:mi>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Como la ampolleta permanece encendida 220 horas, reemplazamos <m:math><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>220</m:mn></m:math>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular el consumo en Wh</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mi>E</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>15</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>220</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>3300</m:mn>
                <m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, el consumo total es 3300 Wh.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Convertir de Wh a kWh</strong></p>
            <p>La equivalencia dada es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1000</m:mn>
                <m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Para pasar de Wh a kWh, dividimos por 1000:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mn>3300</m:mn>
                <m:mtext> Wh</m:mtext>
                <m:mo>÷</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1000</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>3,3</m:mn>
                <m:mtext> kWh</m:mtext>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La ampolleta consume <strong>3,3 kWh</strong> en total cuando permanece encendida durante 220 horas.</p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>ChoiceC</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>